0th-century Indian archaeologists]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Archaeologists of South Asia]]\n\n{{india-scientist-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Akashalan", "label": "safe", "comment": "Image added", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/K._Amarnath_Ramakrishna"}
{"title_page": "New areas", "text_new": "{{About|urban economic zones in China|similar zone in other countries|urban enterprise zone|other uses|New states{{!}}New states (disambiguation)}}\n\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|title = New areas\n|s = {{linktext|\u65b0\u533a}}\n|t = {{linktext|\u65b0\u5340}}\n|p = X\u012bn Q\u016b\n|l = {{nowrap|New Area}}\n}}\n\n{{Administrative levels and divisions of China sidebar}}\n\nThe '''new areas''' or '''new districts''' of the [[China|People's Republic of China]] are new urban districts that are given special economic and development support by the [[Government of China|Chinese Central Government]] or regional government. New areas are divided into two varieties: administrative or management and further divided into levels: state-level, provincial-level, and prefectural-level.\n\n==State-level new areas==\n{{Infobox Chinese\n|title = State-level new areas\n|s = \u56fd\u5bb6\u7ea7\u65b0\u533a\n|t = \u570b\u5bb6\u7d1a\u65b0\u5340\n|p = Gu\u00f3ji\u0101-j\u00ed x\u012bn q\u016b\n|l = {{nowrap|State-level new area}}\n|s2 = {{nowrap|\u56fd\u5bb6\u7ea7\u5f00\u653e\u5f00\u53d1\u65b0\u533a}}\n|t2 = \u570b\u5bb6\u7d1a\u958b\u653e\u958b\u767c\u65b0\u5340\n|p2 = Gu\u00f3ji\u0101-j\u00ed k\u0101if\u00e0ng k\u0101if\u0101 x\u012bn q\u016b\n|l2 = State-level open development new area\n}}\n\nThe State-level new areas of the [[China|People's Republic of China]] are special economic-development zones supported by the central government. The zones are parts of cities at various levels in the formal hierarchy but are known as \"national-level\" or \"state-level\" in reference to the preferential policies and privileges that are granted directly by the State Council. These privileges are to encourage and attract new developments (particularly [[foreign direct investment]]) to speed up the city's economy.<ref>{{cite web|last=Liu|first=Qiang|script-title=zh:\u526f\u7701\u7ea7\u65b0\u533a\u5efa\u8bbe\u98ce\u8d77\uff1a\u884c\u653f\u533a\u5212\u8c03\u6574\u6216\u5c06\u89e3\u51bb\uff1f|url=http://finance.ifeng.com/news/region/20110917/4608846.shtml|work= 21st century economic report ({{lang|zh-hans|21\u4e16\u7eaa\u7ecf\u6d4e\u62a5\u9053}}) |publisher=Ifeng Finance |accessdate=8 September 2012}}</ref>\n\n{|class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\"\n|-\n! Division !! Hanzi ([[Simplified Chinese character|S]]) & [[Pinyin]] !! Designated !! Area<br>(km\u00b2) !! Jurisdiction\n|-\n| [[Pudong|Pudong New Area]]<br>{{small|(administrative)}}\n| \u6d66\u4e1c\u65b0\u533a; P\u01d4d\u014dng X\u012bnq\u016b\n| 11 October 1992<ref>\u56fd\u51fd\u30141992\u3015145\u53f7 {{cite web |script-title=zh:\u4e2d\u534e\u4eba\u6c11\u5171\u548c\u56fd\u884c\u653f\u533a\u5212\uff081992\u5e74\uff09|url=http://www.gov.cn/test/2007-03/23/content_559164.htm|website=\u5168\u56fd\u884c\u653f\u533a\u5212\u4fe1\u606f\u67e5\u8be2\u5e73\u53f0|publisher=Ministry of Civil Affairs of the People's Republic of China|accessdate=20 August 2015}}</ref>\n| 1,210\n| [[Shanghai]] ([[Pudong]])\n|-\n| [[Binhai|Binhai New Area]]<br>{{small|(administrative)}}\n| \u6ee8\u6d77\u65b0\u533a; B\u012bnh\u01cei X\u012bnq\u016b\n| 9 November 2009<ref>\u56fd\u51fd\u30142009\u3015125\u53f7 {{cite web |script-title=zh:\u4e2d\u534e\u4eba\u6c11\u5171\u548c\u56fd\u4e8c\u3007\u3007\u4e5d\u5e74\u53bf\u7ea7\u4ee5\u4e0a\u884c\u653f\u533a\u5212\u53d8\u66f4\u60c5\u51b5|url=http://202.108.98.30/description?dcpid=2009|website=\u5168\u56fd\u884c\u653f\u533a\u5212\u4fe1\u606f\u67e5\u8be2\u5e73\u53f0|publisher=Ministry of Civil Affairs of the People's Republic of China|accessdate=20 August 2015}}</ref>\n| 2,270\n| [[Tianjin]] ([[Binhai]])\n|-\n| [[Liangjiang New Area]]\n| \u4e24\u6c5f\u65b0\u533a; Li\u01cengji\u0101ng X\u012bnq\u016b\n| 18 June 2010<ref>\u56fd\u51fd\u30142010\u301536\u53f7 {{citation|title=Brief Introduction to Liangjiang New Area|url=http://english.liangjiang.gov.cn/2014-01/08/content_17248551.htm|website=Liangjiang New Area|publisher=Liangjiang New Area Government|access